The paper deals with computing high quality node separators in large graphs, which is a problem in distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of evolutionary algorithms and local search algorithms based on maximum flows suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The mention of a scalable communication protocol indicates a possible interest in networked systems (cs.NE) and the use of a multilevel approach suggests a focus on simulation and modeling (cs.SI).
